abstract: Try some cute puppies, some quiet humor or a brutal British mystery show.

abstract: The Florida Supreme Court granted a new “stand your ground” hearing to one defendant and denied the claim of another Thursday as it settled questions on whether a 2017 law should apply retroactively.
snippet: The Florida Supreme Court granted a new “stand your ground” hearing to one defendant and denied the claim of another Thursday as it settled questions on whether a 2017 law should apply retroactively.
lead_paragraph: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. — The Florida Supreme Court granted a new “stand your ground” hearing to one defendant and denied the claim of another Thursday as it settled questions on whether a 2017 law should apply retroactively.
headline_main: Florida Supreme Court Rules on 'Stand Your Ground' Cases
headline_print_headline: Florida Supreme Court Rules on 'Stand Your Ground' Cases

abstract: Speed of over a hundred miles per hour on a curve caused a 2018 crash and fire in Florida that killed the teenage driver of a Tesla Model S and a passenger, federal investigators have concluded.
snippet: Speed of over a hundred miles per hour on a curve caused a 2018 crash and fire in Florida that killed the teenage driver of a Tesla Model S and a passenger, federal investigators have concluded.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Speed of over a hundred miles per hour on a curve caused a 2018 crash and fire in Florida that killed the teenage driver of a Tesla Model S and a passenger, federal investigators have concluded.
headline_main: NTSB Finds Excessive Speed Caused Tesla Crash That Killed 2

abstract: Among cable-news networks, MSNBC came in second and CNN third. But more tuned in to the finales of either ‘Survivor’ or ‘The Masked Singer’ than to any cable news channel.
snippet: Among cable-news networks, MSNBC came in second and CNN third. But more tuned in to the finales of either ‘Survivor’ or ‘The Masked Singer’ than to any cable news channel.
lead_paragraph: As the House of Representatives cast the deciding votes to impeach President Trump on Wednesday, the number of people watching cable news was far greater than usual, according to Nielsen.

abstract: A former model who accused Harvey Weinstein last year of sexually abusing her when she was 16 years old filed a new lawsuit against him Thursday, saying she didn't want to be included in a proposed global settlement that would split $25 million among various accusers.
snippet: A former model who accused Harvey Weinstein last year of sexually abusing her when she was 16 years old filed a new lawsuit against him Thursday, saying she didn't want to be included in a proposed global settlement that would split $25 million am...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A former model who accused Harvey Weinstein last year of sexually abusing her when she was 16 years old filed a new lawsuit against him Thursday, saying she didn't want to be included in a proposed global settlement that would split $25 million among various accusers.
headline_main: Ex-Model Sues Weinstein, Renewing Allegations of Abuse at 16

abstract: When a woman posing as a maternity-ward nurse snatched a newborn from its mother's arms more than 55 years ago, the case made headlines nationwide and led to a massive search by FBI agents and police.

lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — When a woman posing as a maternity-ward nurse snatched a newborn from its mother's arms more than 55 years ago, the case made headlines nationwide and led to a massive search by FBI agents and police.

abstract: After the House voted to impeach President Trump, readers across the United States shared their hopes and fears for the country’s future.
snippet: After the House voted to impeach President Trump, readers across the United States shared their hopes and fears for the country’s future.
lead_paragraph: The United States watched the third president in its history be impeached on Wednesday, prompting a debate among Democrats over when to send charges to the Republican-led Senate.

abstract: Hassan Diab, chosen by the president to form a new government, vowed to work swiftly to slow the country’s collapse.
snippet: Hassan Diab, chosen by the president to form a new government, vowed to work swiftly to slow the country’s collapse.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT, Lebanon — Lebanon’s president appointed a little-known professor and former education minister to form a new government as prime minister on Thursday in the midst of street protests and a financial crisis that have left the country reeling.
